Title: Paris Hilton EDP - 50 ml(For Women)
Description: A luxury scent that oozes an extravagant and bewitching charm for the popular and trend-setting brand of Paris Hilton. For the charming and effervescent woman who is constantly on the move, Paris Hilton EDP is an ideal companion. Created with the joint efforts of James Krivda and Steve Demercado, this Eau de Parfum adds a sparkle to the lovely woman. The top note mixes a juicy combination of fresh peach, ripe apple and fruity hints of melon. Trailing into the heart note, you come across a lovely combination of soft mimose extracts, refreshing and woody freesia, fragrant tuberose, light notes of lily, exotic jasmine and fresh green hints of lily of the valley. This descends into the base note which mixes a heady combination of distinct sandalwood, rich and floral ylang-ylang, soothing musk and organic oakmoss. A vibrant range of ingredients make up this fresh, floral, woody fragrance which you can don at any time of the day. The seductive fragrance comes encased in a cylindrical structure radiating a pink hue and decorated with black vertical waves. The bottle radiates a trendy and upbeat quality that appeals to the modern and fun-loving woman.

Title: Cosderma Lactic Acid Gel Peel 20%(50 ml)
Description: Look around your kitchen and you'll find a handful of natural health remedies, from cough-soothing honey to puffy eye-reducing cucumbers. In fact, your refrigerator may hold a real-life fountain of youth: milk. It contains lactic acid, which is the key to healthy, smooth skin.Lactic acid is an alpha hydroxy acid (AHA). AHAs are acids derived from foods, and, as it turns out a type of acid that's safe to apply to our skin. Citric acid, for example, from citrus fruits (lemons, oranges, etc.) is an alpha hydroxy acid. Lactic acid is found in sour milk, but you may have also heard of or tried other AHAs, such glycolic acid, from sugar cane, which is also a popular ingredient in anti-aging topical skin care products.AHAs applied topically and regularly to your skin help reduce the appearance of aging, and they can be an especially good remedy against fine lines, wrinkles and other signs of premature aging from sun damage. Let's talk about five important benefits -- and the drawbacks -- of adding lactic acid to your skin-care routine, beginning with improved skin texture.
